Anderson recalls Dublin Haka confrontation
Media playback is not supported on this deviceOn the eve of Ireland's autumn international against New Zealand, former Irish captain Willie Anderson recalls the famous confrontation during the All Blacks' pre-match Haka at Lansdowne Road in 1989.The Irish players linked arms and moved towards their opponents.New Zealand, led by skipper Wayne Shelford, won the game 23-6.